---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import LessonNav from "../../components/LessonNav.astro";
import HeroMesh from "../../components/HeroMesh";

const FIPS_CONTRIBUTING = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md";
const FIPS_DESIGN_DOCS = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/tree/master/docs/design";
const FIPS_EXAMPLES = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/tree/master/examples";
const LEARN_FIPS_REPO = "https://github.com/dergigi/learn-fips";
const CORGAN_QUOTE_URL =
  "https://njump.to/nevent1qqsqjkq3yxynqsj7lkk6dst9h4el8yx4rlwysn8pngqewpxk9aqttncpzamhxue69uhhyetvv9ujumn0wvh8xmmrd9skctczyq4m4nj48mlt7kxa2kgjz60e9sgj86mpy8tm5zf0d3gpqjhuxxkw7qcyqqqqqqgg0hv3z";
const FIPS_ANNOUNCEMENT_URL =
  "https://njump.to/nevent1qvzqqqqqqypzq2a6ee2nal4ltrw4tyfpd8ujcyfradsjr4a6pyhkc5qsft7rrt80qyt8wumn8ghj7cn9wehjumn0wd68yvfwvdhk6tcpz4mhxue69uhhyetvv9ujuerpd46hxtnfduhsqgxxce3t2qj4y3qj30qc6a68hcjkhvuh7ua3ktzu04fqe5gmwhgp8spz62cn";
const FIPS_HASHTAG_URL = "https://ants.sh/t/fips";
const SOVENG_PODCAST_URL =
  "https://sovereignengineering.io/podcast/24-building-fips-w-johnathan-corgan";
---

<Base title="Connect and Contribute">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <p class="text-fips-accent font-mono text-sm mb-2">Lesson 14</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Connect and Contribute</h1>

    <section class="space-y-4 text-fips-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-2 mb-4">Ways to help, in order of effort</h2>

      <div class="space-y-3 not-prose my-2">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">Run a node</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Every node you keep online is a new peer someone else can reach. If it stays up for more
            than a day, add it to your bootstrap config so friends can pin you too.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">
            Read a spec and file what you find
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            The <a
              href={FIPS_DESIGN_DOCS}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-fips-accent underline">design docs</a
            > are the ground truth. If a paragraph is unclear, under-specified, or contradicts the code,
            that is a bug worth reporting. This site was written from them, so ambiguities surfaced here
            are worth fixing upstream.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">Ship a small patch</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Walk the <a
              href={FIPS_CONTRIBUTING}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-fips-accent underline">CONTRIBUTING</a
            > guide, then send a focused PR: transport fixes, clippy warnings, docs, integration tests.
            Small PRs get merged fast and teach you the codebase.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">
            Bring an application onto the mesh
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Anything that speaks IPv6 works unmodified. The <a
              href={FIPS_EXAMPLES}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-fips-accent underline">examples</a
            > (Nostr relay, Kubernetes, WireGuard) are good starting points. Your own sidecar is the best
            way to pressure-test the IPv6 adapter.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">Improve this site</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Spot an inaccuracy, a confusing diagram, or a missing lesson? <a
              href={LEARN_FIPS_REPO}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-fips-accent underline">learn-fips</a
            > is MIT-licensed and happy to take PRs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Hear it from the source</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 not-prose my-2">
        <a
          href={FIPS_ANNOUNCEMENT_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">Announcing FIPS</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            Johnathan Corgan's v0.1.0 announcement on Nostr.
          </div>
        </a>
        <a
          href={SOVENG_PODCAST_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">No Solutions #24</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            36-minute walk through the origin story and where the protocol is going next.
          </div>
        </a>
        <a
          href={FIPS_HASHTAG_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">
            <code class="font-mono">#FIPS</code> on Nostr
          </div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            Live hashtag feed of builds, test-node topology, and protocol chatter.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <LessonNav current={14} />
  </article>

  <section class="hex-bg relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="hero-mesh-wrap absolute inset-0">
      <HeroMesh client:load />
      <div class="hero-mesh-fade absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
    </div>
    <figure class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-16 pb-40 md:pb-48">
      <span
        aria-hidden="true"
        class="absolute -top-2 left-4 md:left-6 text-fips-accent font-mono text-6xl leading-none select-none"
        >&ldquo;</span
      >
      <blockquote class="text-fips-text text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed italic">
        <p class="mb-4">
          Engineering solutions to problems is mostly about assembling existing pieces into a new
          whole, more so than inventing a new wheel.
        </p>
        <p>
          FIPS combines known, battle tested concepts going back decades in the fields of
          networking, cryptography, distributed computing, resilient communications, and operating
          systems, with full credit to those who came before.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption class="mt-6 text-sm text-fips-muted font-mono">
        &mdash;
        <a
          href={CORGAN_QUOTE_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-fips-accent hover:underline">Johnathan Corgan</a
        >, author of FIPS
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>
</Base>
